    {
      "unresolved": true,
      "key": {
        "uuid": "dc392131_1dca807c",
        "filename": "encoding/openapi/generate_v2.go",
        "patchSetId": 1
      },
      "lineNbr": 206,
      "author": {
        "id": 1017720
      },
      "writtenOn": "2026-07-02T15:34:05Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "This couples the fold to the default naming: `allNames` is derived from the trimmed selector, but referenced schemas land in `shared` under the name `NamesFunc` assigned. With a custom `NamesFunc` (e.g. upper-casing), a referenced top-level schema is keyed as e.g. \"USED\" in `shared`, so the lookup for \"Used\" misses and the same schema is re-added as a full inline copy — `components.schemas` ends up with both \"USED\" (the $ref target) and \"Used\" (dead duplicate).\n\nRepro: one position referencing `#Used`, `AllSchemas: true`, upper-casing `NamesFunc`. Default `NamesFunc` happens to match the trimmed selector, so the existing tests don\u0027t catch it. Consider routing top-level schemas through the same reference/naming path (or matching by CUERef identity) instead of reconstructing the name.",
      "revId": "6f59a356d0a7ec1fb5ac642b0223a27f7a041c6b",
      "serverId": "d5d70762-12d0-45a1-890d-524b12d3f735"
    },
    {
      "unresolved": false,
      "key": {
        "uuid": "ca561d1e_8709a14e",
        "filename": "encoding/openapi/generate_v2.go",
        "patchSetId": 1
      },
      "lineNbr": 206,
      "author": {
        "id": 1007275
      },
      "writtenOn": "2026-07-03T12:51:49Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "Done. Good catch, thanks. The top-level schemas are now named through the same NamesFunc invocation as the references collected by the generator: a referenced top-level schema is recognized by its root and path (CUERef identity), and a synthetic CUERef is added for each unreferenced one, so the fold no longer reconstructs names and NamesFunc guarantees uniqueness across the whole set. Added v2_all_schemas_namesfunc.txtar covering your repro (AllSchemas + upper-casing NamesFunc with a referenced #Used); it fails without the fix.",
      "parentUuid": "dc392131_1dca807c",
      "revId": "6f59a356d0a7ec1fb5ac642b0223a27f7a041c6b",
      "serverId": "d5d70762-12d0-45a1-890d-524b12d3f735"
    },
    {
      "unresolved": true,
      "key": {
        "uuid": "b58c9196_e6f9e772",
        "filename": "encoding/openapi/testdata/v2_no_all_schemas.txtar",
        "patchSetId": 1
      },
      "lineNbr": 12,
      "author": {
        "id": 1017720
      },
      "writtenOn": "2026-07-02T15:34:05Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "I wonder to myself; the `#` is mainly useful for inline schemas, but for a reference to an existing schema, writing `schema: #: #Used` feels weird. one would naturally write the CUE like `schema: #Used`.",
      "revId": "6f59a356d0a7ec1fb5ac642b0223a27f7a041c6b",
      "serverId": "d5d70762-12d0-45a1-890d-524b12d3f735"
    },
    {
      "unresolved": false,
      "key": {
        "uuid": "3c55d43e_592dab0c",
        "filename": "encoding/openapi/testdata/v2_no_all_schemas.txtar",
        "patchSetId": 1
      },
      "lineNbr": 12,
      "author": {
        "id": 1007275
      },
      "writtenOn": "2026-07-03T12:25:52Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "Yeah, I wondered about this. I decided to do things this way because it makes the distinction between data and schema clear - we can still `cue export` the resulting CUE OpenAPI document as JSON, although the schema parts will be omitted. And not all schemas are inside a `schema` field. Also, it means that the entire document still conforms to the OpenAPI specification, which it would not if the schemas were in place (because the spec specifies a JSON Schema in that position, but the translated schema validates the eventual data, not the schema itself).\n\nFor these reasons, I think it\u0027s probably OK to go ahead as is, at least for the time being. This is all still experimental, so we can change it up if we feel like it.",
      "parentUuid": "b58c9196_e6f9e772",
      "revId": "6f59a356d0a7ec1fb5ac642b0223a27f7a041c6b",
      "serverId": "d5d70762-12d0-45a1-890d-524b12d3f735"
    },
